## Version rules

- New packages start at `"version": "0.0.1"`.
- A `minor` changeset on `0.0.1` produces `0.1.0` (first publish).
- NEVER manually bump `version` — use Changesets only.
- `"private": true` for non-npm packages (demo, test harnesses).

## Changesets

```bash
pnpm run changeset           # create changeset
pnpm run version             # apply changesets → bump versions + CHANGELOGs
pnpm run release             # publish changed packages to npm
```

Every consumer-observable change MUST include a changeset before merge:

- `patch` — bug fixes, internal refactors
- `minor` — new APIs, new packages, new options
- `major` — breaking changes (API removal, rename, behavior change)

## CI checks

```bash
pnpm run build              # must pass
pnpm test                   # must pass
pnpm run lint               # must pass
pnpm run typecheck          # must pass
```
